oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cumberland Gap
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Color woodcut print of the Cumberland Gap depicting the gap in the Appalachian Mountains that pioneers used to reach the western country like Kentucky and Tennessee. Image shows a trail among two tall mountains.
